' Exercises the feature this plan unblocks: a package export with real control
' flow that inline-TRAPs a built-in (`toInt`). Before structured Binary IR this
' could not even build to a package, and the consumer could not lower it.
EXPORT FUNC parseDoubled(s AS String) AS Integer
  IF s = "skip" THEN
    RETURN -1
  END IF
  LET n AS Integer = toInt(s) TRAP(e)
    RETURN -2
  END TRAP
  RETURN n * 2
END FUNC
